{"title_page": "Stefan Campagnolo", "text_new": "{{short description|French footballer}}\n{{Orphan|date=June 2016}}\n\n'''Stefan Campagnolo''' (born 13 March 1969) is a former French [[France|French]] [[football (soccer)|football]]er, who was playing for [[Elite 3000 Fodbold]].<ref>[http://www.helsingor.fodboldhistorie.dk/html/spillere/spillere__elite3000_a-w.htm Elite 3000 Spillerkartotek A - W]</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHis former clubs include [[Lyngby Boldklub]], [[Hellerup IK|HIK]], [[Fremad Amager]] and [[Boldklubben Frem|Frem]].<ref>[http://www.bkfrem.dk/default.asp?id=19&spillerid=93&todo=arkiv Boldklubben Frem profile]</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Campagnolo, Stefan}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French footballers]]\n[[Category:Boldklubben Frem players]]\n[[Category:Lyngby Boldklub players]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n\n\n{{France-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=June 2016}}\n\n'''Stefan Campagnolo''' (born 13 March 1969) is a former French [[France|French]] [[football (soccer)|football]]er, who was playing for [[Elite 3000 Fodbold]].<ref>[http://www.helsingor.fodboldhistorie.dk/html/spillere/spillere__elite3000_a-w.htm Elite 3000 Spillerkartotek A - W]</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHis former clubs include [[Lyngby Boldklub]], [[Hellerup IK|HIK]], [[Fremad Amager]] and [[Boldklubben Frem|Frem]].<ref>[http://www.bkfrem.dk/default.asp?id=19&spillerid=93&todo=arkiv Boldklubben Frem profile]</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Campagnolo, Stefan}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French footballers]]\n[[Category:Boldklubben Frem players]]\n[[Category:Lyngby Boldklub players]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n\n\n{{France-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Red Director", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding localshort description: \"French footballer\", overriding Wikidata description \"French footballer\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stefan_Campagnolo"}
{"title_page": "Kaadhal Oviyam", "text_new": "{{cleanup|date=April 2017|reason=Needs cleanup; synopsis should be in present tense.}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Kadhal Oviyam\n| image = KadhalOviyam.jpg\n| caption = LP vinyl records cover\n| director = [[P. Bharathiraja]]\n| writer =  [[Manivannan]] (dialogues)\n| screenplay = P. Bharathiraja\n| story = [[P. Kalaimani]]\n| starring = Kannan<br>[[Radha (actress)|Radha]]<br>[[Archana (actress)|Archana]]<br>[[Goundamani]]<br>Ramanamoorthy\n| producer = P. Jayarajaa<br>S.P Sigamani\n| music = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| cinematography = [[B. Kannan]]\n| editing = R. Bhaskaran\n| studio = Manoj Creations\n| distributor = Manoj Creations\n| released = 30 April 1982\n| runtime =\n| country = India\n| language = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| budget =\n}}\n\n'''''Kadhal Oviyam''''' (English: Painting of love) is a 1982 Tamil film directed by [[P. Bharathiraja]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Film List Of Director Barathiraja|url=http://www.lakshmansruthi.com/cineprofiles/barathiraja-filmlist.asp|publisher=Lakshman Shruthi|accessdate=22 December 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bharathiraja Profile |url=http://www.jointscene.com/artists/Kollywood/Bharathiraja/114 |publisher=Jointscene |accessdate=22 December 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111219010748/http://www.jointscene.com/artists/Kollywood/Bharathiraja/114 |archivedate=19 December 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinesouth.com/cgi-bin/filmography/newfilmdb.cgi?name=kadhaloviyam|title=Kadhal Oviyam|accessdate=2013-10-08|publisher=cinesouth}}</ref> The film went on to receive critical acclaim but became unsuccessful at the box office.\n\n==Cast==\n* Kannan as Sakthi\n* [[Radha (actress)|Radha]] as Ponni\n* [[Archana (actress)|Archana]]\n* Ramanamoorthy\n* [[Goundamani]]\n* [[Janagaraj]]\n* [[Radha Ravi]]\n* Vellai Subbaiah\n* [[Haja Shareef]]\n* 'Thanjai' Balakrishnan\n* [[Manivannan]]\n* Dhanapal\n* Kamalasekhar\n* [[S. N. Lakshmi]]\n\n==Plot==\nSakthi (Kannan) was an orphan, born in temple and sang devotional hymns for the temple idol. He became blind after an accident. Ponni (Radha) used to hear him singing at the temple and falls in love with him. However, Ponni's mother Vadivukarasai wanted her to marry Radharavi, her relation who had come from  Singapore. Ponni is not willing to marry Radharavi.\n\nPonni performs all of Sakthi's chores without his knowledge. As Sakthi is blind, he is unable to see Ponni, but he can hear Ponni's anklets (an ornament which bharathanatiyam dancers wore on their legs). Once when Sakthi makes a floral offering to the Ambal, they fall on Ponni. From that incident Ponni  thinks that Sakthi is her spouse and breaks to him the news and Sakthi responds positively to the suggestion.\n\nDue to illness, Ponni does not meet Sakthi for three days. When Sakthi comes to know that she is ill, he goes to her house to see her. Her mother discreetly enquires about Sakthi. Ponni says that he is an astrologer and that he is blind. Ponni's  mother informs her worker to give him food as he looked like a beggar. After she leaves, Ponni apologizes to Sakthi for her mother's behaviour and when both talk, Nayanam (Goundamani) hears it and informs Radharavi. Immediately, Radharavi's family goes to Ponni's home for fixing the marriage. But in the engagement, Ponni says that she doesn't like him.\n\nAfter getting frustrated with Ponni's decision, Radharavi's men put Sakthi inside a haystack and set fire to it. Ponni finds him and rescues him, and later they elope together. Both are starving and Ponni wants Sakthi to sing songs for money for their living. While considering Ponni's acclaim, she was kidnapped by some people who smoke marijuana. They tied the hands and legs of Ponni. Meanwhile, Nayanam finds her and takes her back to her home. She gets married to Janagaraj who is a Chettiyar and Dharamakatha (a person managing temple activities) for a famous temple.\n\nSakthi was adopted by a famous singer who arranges eye operation for him and he gets back his vision. He became a famous singer and Janagaraj arranges a temple function and invite Sakthi to sing in that function. Sakthi always thinks of Ponni and searches for her in all the functions where he sang. Sakthi went to Janagaraj's home to stay. Ponni is so stunned after seeing him that she drops his Aarthi plate.\n\nSakthi was too much depressed after Ponni left him. Hearing the love story of Sakthi and Ponni, Janagaraj felt very sad for Sakthi and wants to join him with his lover,  without knowing the real truth that his wife is the lover of Sakthi. Ponni too couldn't say to Sakthi that she is Ponni and she is married. Ponni comes to know that this is the last song Sakthi sings as he won't sing any more songs.\n\nSakthi sings his last song, during the end of the song Ponni wakes up from her seat and walks towards Sakthi in the function. From her salangi sound, Sakthi finds out that she is Ponni. Heavy rain breaks down and all the people run away. But Sakthi continues to sing for which Ponni dance in rain. Ponni knowingly hits pillars of the temples while dancing and dies. After seeing her die, Sakthi touches the Salangai of Ponni, praises it and dies at her feet.\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe music for the film was composed by [[Ilaiyaraaja]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.raaga.com/channels/tamil/moviedetail.asp?mid=T0000072|title=Kadhal Oviyam Songs|accessdate=2013-10-08|publisher=raaga}}</ref> Velli chalangaigal song is in chandrakauns raaga, Naadham En song is set to raaga Abheri.<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/music/of-love-and-longing/article5329771.ece</ref><ref>http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/a-ragas-journey-aspects-of-abheri/article2325286.ece</ref> The song \"Sangeetha Jaathi\" is based on Revathi, Poojaikkaaga vaazhum in Malayamaarudham, Poovil vandu koodum in Mohanam and \"Amma Azhage\" in Malahari raga.<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/music/mystical-revathi/article4418462.ece</ref>\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCF\" align=\"center\"\n| '''No.''' || '''Song''' || '''Singers''' ||'''Lyrics'''\n|-\n| 1 || \"Amma Azhage\" || [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]] || [[Vairamuthu]]\n|-\n| 2 || \"Kuyilae Kuyilae\" || S. P. Balasubrahmanyam, [[S. Janaki]] || [[Panchu Arunachalam]]\n|-\n| 3 || \"Naatham En Jeevanae\" || S. Janaki || rowspan=6|Vairamuthu\n|-\n| 4 || \"Nathiyil Aadum\" || S. P. Balasubrahmanyam, S. Janaki, [[Deepan Chakravarthy]]\n|-\n| 5 || \"Poojaikkaga Vazhum\" || Deepan Chakravarthy\n|-\n| 6 || \"Poovil Vandu\" || S. P. Balasubrahmanyam\n|-\n| 7 || \"Sangeetha Jathimullai\" || S. P. Balasubrahmanyam\n|-\n| 8 || \"Velli Salangaigal\" || S. P. Balasubrahmanyam\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{P. Bharathiraja}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:1982 films]]\n[[Category:Tamil film scores by Ilaiyaraaja]]\n[[Category:Films directed by P. Bharathiraja]]\n[[Category:1980s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic drama films]]\n", "text_old": "{{cleanup|date=April 2017|reason=Needs cleanup; synopsis should be in present tense.}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Kadhal Oviyam\n| image = KadhalOviyam.jpg\n| caption = LP vinyl records cover\n| director = [[P. Bharathiraja]]\n| writer =  [[Manivannan]] (dialogues)\n| screenplay = P. Bharathiraja\n| story = [[P. Kalaimani]]\n| starring = Kannan<br>[[Radha (actress)|Radha]]<br>[[Archana (actress)|Archana]]<br>[[Goundamani]]<br>Ramanamoorthy\n| producer = P. Jayarajaa<br>S.P Sigamani\n| music = [[Ilaiyaraaja]]\n| cinematography = [[B. Kannan]]\n| editing = R. Bhaskaran\n| studio = Manoj Creations\n| distributor = Manoj Creations\n| released = 30 April 1982\n| runtime =\n| country = India\n| language = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| budget =\n}}\n\n'''''Kadhal Oviyam''''' (English: Painting of love) is a 1982 Tamil film directed by [[P. Bharathiraja]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Film List Of Director Barathiraja|url=http://www.lakshmansruthi.com/cineprofiles/barathiraja-filmlist.asp|publisher=Lakshman Shruthi|accessdate=22 December 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bharathiraja Profile |url=http://www.jointscene.com/artists/Kollywood/Bharathiraja/114 |publisher=Jointscene |accessdate=22 December 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111219010748/http://www.jointscene.com/artists/Kollywood/Bharathiraja/114 |archivedate=19 December 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinesouth.com/cgi-bin/filmography/newfilmdb.cgi?name=kadhaloviyam|title=Kadhal Oviyam|accessdate=2013-10-08|publisher=cinesouth}}</ref> The film went on to receive critical acclaim but became unsuccessful at the box office.\n\n==Cast==\n* Kannan as Sakthi\n* [[Radha (actress)|Radha]] as Ponni\n* [[Archana (actress)|Archana]]\n* Ramanamoorthy\n* [[Goundamani]]\n* [[Janagaraj]]\n* [[Radha Ravi]]\n* Vellai Subbaiah\n* [[Haja Shareef]]\n* 'Thanjai' Balakrishnan\n* [[Manivannan]]\n* Dhanapal\n* Kamalasekhar\n* [[S. N. Lakshmi]]\n\n==Plot==\nSakthi (Kannan) was an orphan, born in temple and sang devotional hymns for the temple idol. He became blind after an accident. Ponni (Radha) used to hear him singing at the temple and falls in love with him. However, Ponni's mother Vadivukarasai wanted her to get married to Radharavi, her relation who had come from  Singapore. Ponni is not willing to marry Radharavi.\n\nPonni performs all of Sakthi's chores without his knowledge. As Sakthi is blind, he is unable to see Ponni, but he can hear Ponni's anklets (an ornament which bharathanatiyam dancers wore on their legs). Once when Sakthi makes a floral offering to the Ambal, they fall on Ponni. From that incident Ponni  thinks that Sakthi is her spouse and breaks to him the news and Sakthi responds positively to the suggestion.\n\nDue to illness, Ponni does not meet Sakthi for three days. When Sakthi comes to know that she is ill, he goes to her house to see her. Her mother discreetly enquires about Sakthi. Ponni says that he is an astrologer and that he is blind. Ponni's  mother informs her worker to give him food as he looked like a beggar. After she leaves, Ponni apologizes to Sakthi for her mother's behaviour and when both talk, Nayanam (Goundamani) hears it and informs Radharavi. Immediately, Radharavi's family goes to Ponni's home for fixing the marriage. But in the engagement, Ponni says that she doesn't like him.\n\nAfter getting frustrated with Ponni's decision, Radharavi's men put Sakthi inside a haystack and set fire to it. Ponni finds him and rescues him, and later they elope together. Both are starving and Ponni wants Sakthi to sing songs for money for their living. While considering Ponni's acclaim, she was kidnapped by some people who smoke marijuana. They tied the hands and legs of Ponni. Meanwhile, Nayanam finds her and takes her back to her home. She gets married to Janagaraj who is a Chettiyar and Dharamakatha (a person managing temple activities) for a famous temple.\n\nSakthi was adopted by a famous singer who arranges eye operation for him and he gets back his vision. He became a famous singer and Janagaraj arranges a temple function and invite Sakthi to sing in that function. Sakthi always thinks of Ponni and searches for her in all the functions where he sang. Sakthi went to Janagaraj's home to stay.  Ponni is so stunned after seeing him that she drops his Aarthi plate.\n\nSakthi was too much depressed after Ponni left him. Hearing the love story of Sakthi and Ponni, Janagaraj felt very sad for Sakthi and wants to join him with his lover,  without knowing the real truth that his wife is the lover of Sakthi. Ponni too couldn't say to Sakthi that she is Ponni and she is married. Ponni comes to know that this is the last song Sakthi sings as he won't sing any more songs.\n\nSakthi sings his last song, during the end of the song Ponni wakes up from her seat and walks towards Sakthi in the function. From her salangi sound, Sakthi finds out that she is Ponni. Heavy rain breaks down and all the people run away. But Sakthi continues to sing for which Ponni dance in rain. Ponni knowingly hits pillars of the temples while dancing and dies. After seeing her die, Sakthi touches the Salangai of Ponni, praises it and dies at her feet.\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe music for the film was composed by [[Ilaiyaraaja]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.raaga.com/channels/tamil/moviedetail.asp?mid=T0000072|title=Kadhal Oviyam Songs|accessdate=2013-10-08|publisher=raaga}}</ref> Velli chalangaigal song is in chandrakauns raaga, Naadham En song is set to raaga Abheri.<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/music/of-love-and-longing/article5329771.ece</ref><ref>http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/a-ragas-journey-aspects-of-abheri/article2325286.ece</ref> The song \"Sangeetha Jaathi\" is based on Revathi, Poojaikkaaga vaazhum in Malayamaarudham, Poovil vandu koodum in Mohanam and \"Amma Azhage\" in Malahari raga.<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/music/mystical-revathi/article4418462.ece</ref>\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCF\" align=\"center\"\n| '''No.''' || '''Song''' || '''Singers''' ||'''Lyrics'''\n|-\n| 1 || \"Amma Azhage\" || [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]] || [[Vairamuthu]]\n|-\n| 2 || \"Kuyilae Kuyilae\" || S. P. Balasubrahmanyam, [[S. Janaki]] || [[Panchu Arunachalam]]\n|-\n| 3 || \"Naatham En Jeevanae\" || S. Janaki || rowspan=6|Vairamuthu\n|-\n| 4 || \"Nathiyil Aadum\" || S. P. Balasubrahmanyam, S. Janaki, [[Deepan Chakravarthy]]\n|-\n| 5 || \"Poojaikkaga Vazhum\" |